## Git Commit Conventions

### Commit Message Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body>

<footer>
```

### Types

| Type | Description | Example |
|------|-------------|---------|
| `feat` | New feature | `feat({{PRIMARY_ENTITY_LOWER}}): add pagination support` |
| `fix` | Bug fix | `fix(form): prevent submit with invalid data` |
| `refactor` | Code refactoring | `refactor(repositories): segregate read/write operations` |
| `style` | Code style changes | `style(screens): format code with dart format` |
| `docs` | Documentation | `docs(guides): add architecture documentation` |
| `test` | Test changes | `test(usecases): add tests for add {{PRIMARY_ENTITY_LOWER}}` |
| `chore` | Build/tooling | `chore(deps): upgrade riverpod to 3.3.1` |

### Examples

```bash
# Feature
git commit -m "feat({{PRIMARY_ENTITY_LOWER}}): add infinite scroll pagination

- Add paginated provider
- Implement load more functionality
- Update UI to show loading indicator

Closes #123"

# Bug fix
git commit -m "fix(validation): prevent negative nominal input

- Add validator for negative amounts
- Show error message for invalid input

Fixes #456"

# Refactor
git commit -m "refactor(repositories): segregate {{SECONDARY_ENTITY_LOWER}} repositories

- Split {{SECONDARY_ENTITY_LOWER}} repository into 4 focused interfaces:
  - {{SECONDARY_ENTITY}}ReadRepository
  - {{SECONDARY_ENTITY}}WriteRepository
  - {{SECONDARY_ENTITY}}ManagementRepository
  - {{SECONDARY_ENTITY}}SeedingRepository
- Create adapter for backward compatibility

Follows SRP and ISP principles"
```

