## Code Review Checklist

### Functionality
- [ ] Does the code implement the requirements?
- [ ] Are edge cases handled (null, empty, zero)?
- [ ] Is error handling appropriate?
- [ ] Are validations in place?

### Architecture
- [ ] Does it follow Clean Architecture?
- [ ] Are dependencies inverted (depend on abstractions)?
- [ ] Are interfaces segregated (small, focused)?
- [ ] Is SRP followed (single responsibility)?

### Code Quality
- [ ] Is code readable and self-documenting?
- [ ] Are magic numbers/strings replaced with constants?
- [ ] Is DRY principle followed (no duplication)?
- [ ] Are naming conventions followed?

### Testing
- [ ] Are unit tests included for business logic?
- [ ] Are widget tests included for UI?
- [ ] Is test coverage adequate?

### Documentation
- [ ] Are public APIs documented?
- [ ] Are complex algorithms explained?
- [ ] Are TODOs commented with issue links?

### Performance
- [ ] Are expensive operations optimized?
- [ ] Are builds and const constructors used?
- [ ] Are unnecessary rebuilds avoided?

